To create a simple website that displays a random joke from a list of four jokes when a user clicks a button, you can use HTML for the structure, CSS for styling (if needed), and JavaScript to handle the random joke selection and display. Below is a basic example of how you could implement this:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Random Joke Generator</title>
<style>
  body {
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: center;
    align-items: center;
    height: 100vh;
    flex-direction: column;
  }
  #jokeContainer {
    margin-top: 20px;
    padding: 20px;
    border: 1px solid #ddd;
    border-radius: 5px;
  }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<button id="jokeButton">Tell me a joke</button>
<div id="jokeContainer"></div>

<script>
  // List of jokes
  var jokes = [
    "Why don't scientists trust atoms? Because they make up everything.",
    "Why did the chicken go to the séance? To talk to the other side.",
    "I told my wife she was drawing her eyebrows too high. She looked surprised.",
    "Parallel lines have so much in common. It’s a shame they’ll never meet."
  ];

  // Function to display a random joke
  function displayRandomJoke() {
    var randomIndex = Math.floor(Math.random() * jokes.length);
    var joke = jokes[randomIndex];
    document.getElementById('jokeContainer').innerText = joke;
  }

  // Event listener for the button
  document.getElementById('jokeButton').addEventListener('click', displayRandomJoke);
</script>

</body>
</html>
```

This code does the following:

1. Sets up a basic HTML structure with a button and a container to display the joke.
2. Includes a small amount of CSS to center the content and style the joke container.
3. Defines a JavaScript array with four jokes.
4. Creates a function `displayRandomJoke` that selects a random joke from the array and displays it in the `jokeContainer` element.
5. Adds an event listener to the button that triggers the `displayRandomJoke` function when clicked.

You can copy and paste this code into an HTML file and open it in a web browser to see it in action. When you click the "Tell me a joke" button, a random joke from the list will be displayed on the page.
